**Escalation vs dead letter**

- **EscalateToHuman** — agent did useful work, got stuck, partial branch handed to human as starting point
- **DeadLetterEscalate** — infrastructure broke, task goes back to DLQ for retry or manual handling

---

**Branch hierarchy**

```
main (production)
    ↑ manual human promotion only

dev/testing
    ↑ human verification gate

ghost (ephemeral, created on demand)
    ↑ automated promotion on passing threshold
    ↑ destroyed after promotion attempt

agent branches
    ↑ merge queue picks up, tests against ghost
```

**Ghost branch lifecycle**

```
Trigger (queue limit or time window)
    → create ghost from dev/testing
    → check conflicts via get_merge_conflicts()
    → speculatively merge queued PRs in order
    → CI runs against ghost
    → if passes → squash to dev/testing, destroy ghost
    → if fails → remove bad PR, rerun remaining
    → ghost destroyed either way
```

**Ghost trigger rules**

- Queue depth hits batch limit → create ghost, process batch
- Time window expires → create ghost, process whatever is queued
- Whichever comes first

